# LocalGen GPT-image-1 UI Project Overview

This is a React-based web application for generating AI images using OpenAI's GPT-image-1 model. It's built with:

- React (via Preact for lightweight implementation)
- TypeScript
- Vite as the build tool
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Jotai for state management
- Radix UI components with custom styling
- Framer Motion for animations

## Project Structure

- `/src/components`: UI components organized by feature and common UI elements
  - `/ui`: Shared UI components (buttons, cards, inputs, etc.)
  - `/ImageGeneration`: Components for the image generation feature
  - `/History`: Components for image history display
  - `/Layout`: Structural components (header, etc.)
  - `/Settings`: Settings-related components
- `/src/hooks`: Custom React hooks for reusable logic
- `/src/store`: State management with Jotai atoms, actions, reducers
- `/src/types`: TypeScript type definitions
- `/src/lib`: Utility functions and shared logic
- `/src/config`: Configuration constants and defaults
- `/src/assets`: Static assets

## Main Features

- Image generation with configurable options
- Image history and management
- OpenAI API integration
- Cost estimation for generated images
- Responsive design for various screen sizes
